OL,3,CHospitality industry predicts job
OL,4,Closses as minimum wage increases
OL,6,FEach year, the Living Wage Commission
OL,7,Fgathers information on what sort of
OL,8,Flevel of increase to the minimum wage
OL,9,Frates the economy can sustain without
OL,10,Fdestroying jobs.
OL,12,FIts recommendations tend to be
OL,13,Faccepted by the business lobby, albeit
OL,14,Fwith the odd grumble.
OL,16,FThis year, an increase in the National
OL,17,FLiving Wage rise from #11.44 to #12.21
OL,18,Fan hour from next April - an increase
OL,19,Fof 6.7% - is judged to be a fair and
OL,20,Fpain-free settlement.
