OL,3,CHospitality industry predicts job
OL,4,Closses as minimum wage increases
OL,6,FHospitality UK represents 700 pubs,
OL,7,Fbars, restaurants and hotels which
OL,8,Fcollectively employ 3.2 million people.
OL,10,FKate Nicholls, the chief executive,
OL,11,Fsays the changes to the minimum wage
OL,12,Frates and national insurance will add
OL,13,F#1.5 billion to the wage bills of her
OL,14,Fmembers.
OL,16,F"The consequences will be lower
OL,17,Fprofits, lower business investment,
OL,18,Fhigher prices for consumers, fewer
OL,19,Fhours for workers and some smaller,
OL,20,Findependent businesses will fail,"
OL,21,FNicholls says.
